\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 I never had any worries I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh very easy to get on with too, and he was very - no, never had show of bad temper, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did he show affection to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. We weren't very demonstrative. Than my mother - but not otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 If you had any worries would you share them with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh yes. We were all - one and one you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 How did they expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did your parents bring you up in a certain way to behave towards your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No I don't remember them making any - you know - we - we - just took for granted. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Never. Never s
aid that, we weren't - you know - were so - we weren't a bit quarrel - some. We had a lot of fun, we used to - take for instance if we quarre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2370473\charrsid12417786 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 led it'd be something about a toy or something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 What kind of people do you think your pare
nts hoped you would grow up to be? Did they emphasise your character or were they keen on what jobs you all had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh they wanted us to have a good job. Oh they wanted us to - yes, and my dad wanted us to - live a good life and go to chapel wherever we
 were. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 What do you think they considered the important things in life, did they bring you up to think some things more important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh I don't think - no, only that we - that we were kind to each other and - did good deeds and anything good f
or others I think, that was their idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 What did they think of swearing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 We never swore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 They wouldn't allow that in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 When the grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 I don't know that - I don't remember much about that sort of thing you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Sent to bed. That was a big punish - punishment. Oh it was awful to go to bed and you'd cry, get in bed and cry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 They wouldn't smack you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. We did have a couple of smacks mind but - that wasn't - yes, for talking in chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Who would smack you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 My mother, not my father would never smack us. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would your father and mother send you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2370473\charrsid12417786 I don't think my father interfe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 red with any that part of our lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Do you remember a particular instance when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Nothing. No. No, when I look back about - things like that, no I don't either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You said you used to cry when you were sent to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You don't remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would you say that you received the ideas that you had on how to behave from your father and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh yes, from the both of them. They were verymuch the same you know, we were all in all sort of -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 If you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh pancakes. Always - always pancakes and Welsh cakes. There was no birthday cake you see. Pancakes and Welsh cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would you receive presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No I don't - I don't remember anything. Books. A book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 And the special thing you had to eat would be pancakes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would you have anybody there, any guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No, there were enough guests ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Can you remember doing anything on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh we used to have a lovely Christmas Day. Lovely Christmas - always - we always had a turkey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You always went to chapel on Christmas night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes, we had to - you see, lovely - very interesting, that was on Christmas night. But I've forgotten now I'm sure. It was a long time ago.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 That was the only thing you felt was really special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You said you had a piano in the house, how many of you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 
And strangely enough - a friend of my father's - his name was Johnny Davis, and he was the storekeeper on the - in the colliery, and they were great friends, and he used to come to the house to give us lessons. And my sister
 Gwladys and I - had lessons together. Then later on Mair and - and I don't know, it was Rhiannon probably having lessons, I don't remember much about that, but Gwladys and I had - oh and he used to be very cross with us. He used to tell us - your father 
paying for your lessons for you you know, he said, and you don't try to practice. You must practice more. Always having a row for not practicing. Well we used to quarrel before he came to practice before he came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did anyone in the family sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Not - nobody had a singing voice. Mother - had a nice voice really. But none of us were interested in singing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 We had a lot of - singing round the piano. An awful lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 
In the - in the nights you know. Nove - lovely lot of singing piano, specially - on holiday times and Christmas time we'd be around that piano. And I know - wasn't a good player but I could manage sort of thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 I don't remember much playing games. We used to play hide and seek and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh - more books than you like. My mother - used to really cross - with my father for buying books, and the
re were no room to keep them you see. Every - every space was filled up with bookcases. And in the end do you know what he used to do? He used to buy a book, keep it in his pocket, and not show it you know, for a long time then it would come out. And join
 the rest of the books that were there. Oh - oh - oh hundreds there were. You see that cabinet here there. Well my - these are valuable today. I want to talk to - oh no, now this is - is grand -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did you have any newspapers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes, what
 was it called in those days. Western - there was Western Mail. What was the Tory paper called? There was a Tory paper that time, I don't remember the name of it now. Yes, Tory paper, wait a bit, what was the other paper. There was another paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You had two daily newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. One. Only one. And I don't remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would you have any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Cymru'r Plant. Trysorfa Plant. Cymru Mawr. Here they are look. Bound all of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Do you remember your father reading, or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 
Oh my father, they were terrible readers. My mother liked reading too. But I didn't see her, she didn't have time much to read. Look at that, that's interesting. That's my brother's wife where we went - to Germany.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did your father and mother ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No, I think we were taught to read - to read so young that - you know, we got on with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 I remember quite well. In law you know, you're not to talk English anymore. You're not 
to talk Welsh any - not to talk English you see. Well there'd be dead silence for hours. We wouldn't talk at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 That was in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 In the house, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would you remember a funeral in the family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 The only time - first 
time I remember seeing my father crying - was - when we buried the little baby and she only six months old she was. And she had a convulsion and died I saw my father cry - over that baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did you go to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. We did - it was a private 
funeral, and a tiny little coffin, I can see it now. It was taken away with the - undertaker and my father and the man next door here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Nobody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. And the minister and a preacher. And that was Doctor Philips.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would there be any mourning, did they wear mourning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. No I don't think - don't remember. Oh yes we did, we had black dresses. We had lovely black dresses and white bows in our hair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You don't remember another funeral at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes. Well now - yes, yes, I remember my brother's funeral, he was killed you know in the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 That was later on though wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No other funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Were you taken out visiting neighbours at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You didn't mix with the other people around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. We didn't have relatives you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 What about neighbours? Or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Isn't funny, I just cannot -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You didn't go visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. People used to visit us, Mr and Mrs Tommy Davis. He was a Rac
cobite too and he used to go to conferences with my father. And they used to come, 'cos they only had one child and they could bring him with 'em you see. But we were too many to go to their house. Having to walk up Ferndale was a good mile and - used to 
come down regularly. Every week. And my father used to go to conferences you see with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. I don't think so. No, we were sent for shopping you know down to the grocer down the road. Well - well the Co-operative you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would you go with your mother to buy shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 
Oh yes, go and be - try them on you know. And we would - we'd go to the - the Co-op, the butcher always and there was a - oh, thoroughly English man there. And I remember my brother once going shop
ping and having a - coming back with two big - rounds of beef, ribs you know, you call them, ribs of beef but my mother said - that she didn't want the ribs and she took them back, but he wouldn't take them back so we had to have two ribs of beef that day
, I've never forgotten that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 So you used to go and do shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes. Oh yes, did a bit of shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You wouldn't go shopping with your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. We - we went together
 all - well we went - there were times when we would go with only my father, yes, but - never anywhere special, only up the mountain. Up to Penrhys mountain, oh walk miles we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Do you remember any outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 And we used to go wimb}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690821\charrsid12417786 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 rrying. Picking wimberries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 With your father or with your mother or with both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Not - not both. - we children alone would go wimberrying, yes. Oh lovely, behind us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Do you remember any outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 But we never landed back with many w
imberries you know, not enough to make a tart, we would have lost them and - tumbled. Did I remember what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Any outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Sunday school outings the side - seaside you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 What about Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No, we never - didn't go away on Bank Holidays, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did you ever go away on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 
What I can remember one thing about a holiday - one holiday. And don't - it was a - we were taken - to visit an uncle and aunt who lived in Porth. And - we were taken by train you see, there were no
 trams in those days. Were taken by train and when we got out - of the station, I can remember my father asking the - the porter - what time is the train going back? You see. Giving time for us to have tea and things first. He said, don't worry about goin
g
 back, he said, go and see the fire. And there's an ironmongery stores there right by the station, was burnt. And my father was fascinated and we children were terrified. We were afraid that he would go to the fire too near, and that we wouldn't see him a
gain. We were terrified, so we - we didn't enjoy looking on at that fire because we were - too upset about it. And we'd walk back - we'd walk back sometimes all the way from Porth you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would you go away on holiday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 To Aberystwyth, yes, in the summer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 How often, would you go regularly every summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 
Only in the - in the summer, yes, when - as long as my grandparents were alive we went when we were - when were older and that age, that Mair - when they were younger ones came - we didn't. Only go with my brother and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Only when you were younger, when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 How long would you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 For a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 How many of you went, just Meredith and you and your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes. No, my
 father - my mother would be home with the rest of the children. Yes. And we always went to - they lived in Cwmrheidol and my - we used to go to - to town on the market day, sit up on the castle, you know, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 How would you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Eren bach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would your father take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 
Yes, yes, my father would take us and we could play on the castle grounds. And I can always remember about the last time - it was the war, the first world war had happened and my uncle - had then - returned from Ca
nada, after being out at Canada for years and years, his name was Enoch. And he came back home. And now - for a holiday he meant to come. But you see, the young men were being called up. Well he didn't want to go to the Army, he was very shy, quiet man. A
n
d so of course the result was that he had to go down the mines. And he came down to Tylorstown, my father found lodgings with him with an old lady who was a widow and that was her job you know, keeping lodgers, to earn her - her livelihood. And - I can re
m
ember the morning quite well. Somebody running up the house to tell my father - that my uncle had been killed. He had - gone down the pit. And a fall - he was just only just gone in to the mine. And a fall came and killed him instantly. And the funny thin
g
 I can remember most of all is - that - following summer, there was the talk about miners strikes and all this and my father was sitting with us children on the castle grounds where, you know, loved to sit and look over the sea and I - we always went out 
i
n a boat - in - had a sail on the sea, very fond of the sea. And then we'd sit there and play about and this man - started running down the miners because they were coming out on strike. And of course when he got home that day, when we got home to the hou
s
e there was this telegram to say that my uncle had been killed. And his one desire - was to go back in the train to the castle, look for that man and ram this - telegram at him and tell him now - that's the life of a miner. You'll never know. And - and he
 was always sorry that he ever saw that man again to tell him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 And that happened while you were on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes. Well it broke my grandparents, they were awfully upset by it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would it be only Meredith and you would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Only Meredith and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 The rest of the family wouldn't go on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Well you see, they wouldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 But as they got older they would go would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 We were all grown up then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 What sort of things did you do when you went away, you went out in a boat regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Always had a boat, yes. Yes. That was a great treat. Otherwise playing in the grounds you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 It was outside Aberystwyth you'd be staying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes, in Cwnrheidol. Not far from Penllywyn you know. You know, where the -
 the railway station, aberffrwd it's called, and the chapel, Presbyterian chapel is there. And in there my grandmother, my grandfather - my uncle Enoch who was killed in the pit was buried there, my auntie. She died young - four - oh there's about five bu
ried in a grave there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would you go on the beach and in the water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes. Yes, we wouldn't go in the water, we weren't fond - no. We paddled perhaps but we wouldn't bathe ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Anything else you remember doing on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 We loved having
 - tea somewhere, I don't remember the place where we used to go. Don't remember, we used to have a great for tea and I don't remember what it was now, isn't it funny, I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did you spend Saturday differently in those days when you were young?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. I don't think - we just played and - read a lot and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 You didn't go anywhere special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Cwrdd trwy'r dydd. All afternoon and night. Afternoon - yes, chapel and Sunday school and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Would you wear different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh best clothes always on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Shoes and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes. Oh different, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did you play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No I don't remember ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690821\charrsid12417786  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 being allowed to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did - your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 
I don't think they were that strict about it but - I don't remember any - anything much about - Sunday fussing, no, we weren't allowed to go out to play - you know, in the streets or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 
Nearly always. My mother never went in the morning because she was cooking dinner you see. But she was - would be there in the night always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 And your father would be there all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Oh, all day long. An
d he was always teaching Sunday - the class, Sunday school class up - up to the time that he died he taught a class, big class of young - girls and boys - girls you know. Always. And we had holi you know, we used to join together in the end and there'd be
 holi - holi - question}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690821\charrsid12417786 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 aire you see. Yes, every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Was it the Welsh Presbyterian?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Yes. It's there still poor things and there's not many members there now. They've a beautiful pipe organ there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 How often would your father and mother go to chapel, the weeknight as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 My father would go to every service. Everything that was going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 And your mother would go on the weeknights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 No. She always had babies in the house. There'd be Monday night, cwrdd gweddi. Cwrdd B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10690821\charrsid12417786 aby}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786  ieuanc, Nos Fawrth, Bible class in Merthyr, Seit Dydd Iau, Raccobites, why I' am a Raccobite on Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 So it was only Saturday you didn't go to chapel?
