etimes we went - we once - I remember going to Penarth. And then a great treat and living in Tylorstown were very much in the news when they took us to Western. On the boat to Western. And there was one year - when - we arrived too late, the tide had - go
n
e out you see, and we couldn't land. And the thrill was - to be taken off the big boat, the Cambrian boat you know, and put - into little boats to get to shore. I remember that, and we were very young then. Of course we were terrified. Going down in a lit
tle boat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13510004 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 But you had a nice day did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2432619 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7092875\charrsid12417786 Lovely. Every year Sunday school outings.
